      "text": "Parsons […] sees the organism as that component of action by which action adapts to external conditions or also seeks long-term equilibria with external ecological conditions. This is not uninteresting especially among recent interests in relations between action or even society and ecology. It tells us, in fact, that ecology, the environment, affects action only in the sense that it affects the \"behavioral organism,\" that is, it disturbs some aspect, and not the cultural aspect, of action or requires adjustments at that level. (Luhmann, Einführung in die Systemtheorie, p. 29)"
